oblem]]: \'\'What is the wild Pokémon that came to our [[Paniola Ranch|ranch]] in today\'s episode?\'\'\n** Host: {{an|Kiawe}}\n** Choices: {{p|Growlithe}}, {{p|Kangaskhan}}, {{p|Garchomp}}, {{p|Seismitoad}}\n** Answer: Kangaskhan\n* The English dub was released on [[Google Play]] on April 10, 2019, 17 days before the episode aired in {{pmin|the United States}}.\n* Kiawe, {{an|Mallow}}, {{an|Lillie}}, and {{Ash}} narrate the preview for the [[SM104|next episode]].\n* The pose {{an|Brock}} and [[Olivia]] make when using {{m|Continental Crush}} is a reference to the Erupting Burning Finger Sekiha Love-Love Tenkyoken from the anime series \'\'{{wp|Mobile Fighter G Gundam}}\'\'. The mecha {{TRT}} uses is a reference to the Dark Gundam from the same series.\n** Coincidentally, this is the second time in the {{pkmn|anime}} where \'\'Mobile Fighter G Gundam\'\' is referenced in an episode where Brock and Misty make guest appearances, the first occurring in \'\'[[SM042|Alola, Kanto!]]\'\'.\n* {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Stufful}} appearing riding on a toy {{alo|Exeggutor}} is a reference to Odate Buta from the anime series {{wp|Yatterman}}.\n* This episode marks the first time Brock has obtained a new Pokémon since his {{TP|Brock|Happiny|Chansey}}, [[DP038|538 episodes ago]].\n* Music from \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\' is used as background music.\n* {{an|Brock}} and {{an|Misty}} read the [[Who\'s That Pokémon?]] segment in the dub.\n\n===Errors===\n* After the {{tc|Hiker}}s photobomb Rotom\'s group photo, the Poké Ball design on Ash\'s hat is missing.\n* At the end of Brock and Olivia\'s execution of Continental Crush, when adding "in love", Olivia\'s mouth moves, though she doesn\'t speak. \n** This is corrected in the English dub, in which both Brock and Olivia say "crush on you".\n\n===Dub edits===\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Epilang|color=90BDDC|bordercolor=F1912B\n|zh_cmn={{tt|粉碎岩石的熱血之心！麗姿和小剛！！|A Passionate Heart That Can Smash Even Rock! Olivia and Broc